title: High School Football: Four questions for Week 7
text:
MORE It is getting late in the season, so the games take on added importance with the cutoff date for qualification for the NJSIAA playoffs looming on Nov. 7 and the start of the NJSIAA playoffs on Nov. 13.
Power points, seeding for the playoffs and home field advantage for the playoffs will be determined the next three weekends.
Week 7 of the Shore Conference season brings us some fascinating nondivisional games.
Middletown South, which has been ranked No. 1 in the Asbury Park Press Top 10 since the start of the season, faces a test Friday night when it meets No. 6 Brick Memorial at Brick Memorial's DiFabio Field.
Red Bank Catholic, ranked No. 8 in the Asbury Park Press Top 10, and Manalapan are not the teams they were last year when they met in one of the most ballyhooed games in recent Shore Conference history, but they are still teams capable of making runs in the respective sectional playoffs heading into their game Friday night at Manalapan.
